The inscription is placed on three different parts of the vessel, divided as follows: 
                                        1) a first text on the inside of the rim of the vessel, arranged in a circle, boustrophedon; 
                                        2) a second text identical to the first arranged on the body of the vessel in three lines, boustrophedon; 
                                        3) a third text on the opposite side of the body, in two lines, boustrophedon.
